### ðŸŽ“ Role in AMCB Architecture
This layer represents the **Root of Trust (Physical Authentication Stage)** described in the AMCB model.  
Instead of assuming abstract device identity, **a real PUF logic circuit was designed to generate 5 unique hardware response keys**.

### ðŸ§© Stage 1 â€” PUF Circuit Identity Generation
- A **hardware-inspired logic circuit (PUF)** was manually constructed.
- **5 device-specific PUF responses** were extracted from it.
- These represent **real CPS fingerprint identities**, not randomly generated keys.

